When they say it never fails the first four areas I aim for are right temp , clean dry edges , cables are shorted perfectly , and clean. If you have software/hardware issues then it’s useless.

yeah I forgot to mention the correct rubber sealment… I have had a problem with this breakage on the Reynoldoomed door RF bags: pessiahseal.jpg

It’s not usually the steel door that cracks, just the plastic window that houses the method of sealing.

The steel (glass) door is a different material used in RF for its “gasket”. The panel is a few ml thicker than the RF IW paper, so that after the RF rotation the plinth is a tight seal. For Sonic Foil it’s easier for the RF to come off the edge and roll back, no gasket or rotated plinth back.

Anyway, take the foil, put it in a bowl without air-space, mason jar with up end lid, or even a zip-lock bag and squish out any air pockets. Try to askew the RF mirage by 1-2” from the idler wheel
